# `lightning` — agent guide template

> Drop-in template for an agent CLAUDE.md when working in
> the `lightning` package or a fork of it. Mirrors
> `CLAUDE.md.foundation` (cross-package conventions) and
> specialises it for the clightning-only educational
> Lightning frontend.

## 1. Scope

`lightning` is the Lightning Network frontend targeting
**clightning (Core Lightning)** as the single backend, plus
vendored BOLT / LNURL / LSPS specs and a small JSON API at
`.well-known/lightning/<user>/`. lnd and phoenixd support
are explicitly out of scope; the libexec verb-dispatch
layout leaves the door open for future backends but ships
only the clightning plugin.

Out of scope:

- on-chain operations (clightning's bitcoind connection
  handles them; the JSON API never moves on-chain funds)
- custodial wallets (non-custodial by default)
- lnd / phoenixd support

## 2. Repo conventions

Standard rpk per-package: `bin/lightning` dispatcher plus
libexec lookup for verbs (`libexec/lightning/<verb>`). The
clightning calls live directly under those verb scripts —
no extra "backend plugin" layer.

Educational package: vendors BOLT 1..12 + LNURL LUDs +
Lightning Address spec + the local Well-Known API spec
under `share/doc/lightning/standards/`.

## 3. Issue authoring

Same as `CLAUDE.md.foundation`. **Bugs come before features
at the same priority level.**

## 4. The no-shared-lib policy

`lightning` calls only `account` at runtime (for wallet
remote URLs). The on-chain leg of channel opens is handled
by clightning itself (its built-in bitcoind connection); we
never shell out to the `bitcoin` package directly. Verb
scripts call only `lightning-cli`.

Externally we depend on:

- `python3` — for the Apache CGI scripts at
  `.well-known/lnurlp/` (FEAT-176) and
  `.well-known/lightning/` (FEAT-196).
- `sqlite3` — for the per-wallet store (FEAT-193).
- `jq` — for JSON reshaping in verb scripts.

The shell verbs remain the source of truth; Python is a
thin HTTP frontend that shells out.

## 5. Three-user separation (system-mode)

On `lightning daemon install --system`:

| User         | Role                                                       |
|--------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `clightning` | runs `lightningd`; owns `/var/lib/clightning/`             |
| operator     | runs `lightning` CLI; owns the wallet repo + secret store; |
|              | added to group `clightning` on install                     |
| `www-data`   | runs Apache + the CGI scripts; bridges to operator via     |
|              | a narrow sudoers fragment                                  |

The RPC socket is mode 0660, group `clightning`. Apache is
not in that group; the CGI scripts cross the privilege
boundary via `sudo -u <operator> lightning api-* <args>`
with argument-shape validation enforced both in sudoers and
the `api-*` verbs themselves.

## 6. What is intentionally duplicated

- **Verb-level command construction** — each verb script
  shells out to `lightning-cli` inline; no shared cli-helper
  library.
- **Invoice / payment-hash parsing** — implemented in each
  verb that needs it.
- **CGI endpoint scripts** — one Python file per endpoint
  (FEAT-196), only `_lib.py` shared. Endpoint scripts don't
  reach across each other.

## 7. Build / install

`./configure && make install`. Stow-based.

Optional add-ons (operator opts in explicitly):

- `make install-skills-user` — symlinks
  `skills/lightning-wallet/` into agent skill directories.
- `make install-apache-bridge` — drops the sudoers fragment
  and Apache vhost snippet for the JSON API.

## 8. Versioning

Semver. The root `VERSION` file is the source of truth.
`tests/unit/lightning.bats` is the contract.
